config.text:
Add External Data


Click the Add External Data button to add your own data to the map from ArcGIS, a URL, or a file. After the widget opens, use Click to Add Data to open the external data options. Click the Search, URL, or File tabs, depending on how you want to add your dataset.

Add Gateway Data


Click the Add Layers to Map button to add available dataset layers. Click the Browse and Search tabs within the widget to explore data. Click More Info under the layer name to learn more. Click the plus sign next to the layer name to add to the map.

Draw on the Map


Click on Draw to make your own notes and drawings on the map. Select your desired drawing mode. Choose the desired options for the selected draw mode. Click on the map to begin drawing. Click Clear all to erase all drawings from the map.

Use the Legend


After adding data layers to the map, open the Legend and click the arrow above the layer name to expand. Note the options in the box to the right of the layer name and symbology.

Print Your Map


Use Print to make a printout of the map as it looks on your screen. Update the settings as you would like. Click the Print Result tab to view your printout.

Basemap and Measure


Use the Basemap gallery to change the basemap. The Measure tool measures length and area, as well as getting the coordinates of a point.

Share Your Map


To share the current map for others to interact with, click Share in the upper right corner. Map layers you added to the Legend will show in the widget and will be included in the shared map. Click Create Shareable Link to generate the URL. Then click the link to copy to the clipboard.
